&lt;p&gt;Pearce is seeking experienced Commercial HVAC Technicians to join our team for servicing and repairing heavy commercial HVAC equipment. This is a fast-paced and rewarding job that is best suited for individuals who are responsible, self-directed, highly motivated, willing to travel, and looking to learn and grow in the HVAC industry. This is a regional position. Candidates should reside in the Sacramento, California area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining heavy commercial HVAC equipment including chillers, water cooled systems, receptacle compressors, Liebert systems, controls, and multiple cooling systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnosing, troubleshooting, repairing, or installing and replacing components of entire systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting performance checks and regular maintenance on split systems up to 20 tons.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing additional maintenance or upgrades to out-of-season heavy commercial HVAC equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responding to service calls in a timely manner, including emergency call out services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Timely and accurate completion of daily work reports.&lt;/li&gt;
